  "text": "The structure of this paper is as follows: In section 2 we review the conditions that renormalized operators must meet for the construction of [CITATION_1] to be valid and provide a description of our initial approach. In section 3 we study the space of all possible renormalization schemes at second order in the deformation parameter. In section 4 we consider the cubic order. In section 5 we consider all orders for a particular two-parameter family of renormalization schemes and prove that all the conditions set out by [CITATION_2] are satisfied for this family. In section 6 we discuss which of the free parameters present in the renormalization scheme actually affect the SFT solution and how. Finally, we propose the existence of an even larger family of solutions. Appendix C contains the proof of an important technical result necessary to prove the first BRST condition of [CITATION_3] which was not included in that paper.",
